{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I have been teaching for a long time,"},{"time":3000,"text":"and in doing so"},{"time":5000,"text":"have acquired a body of knowledge about kids and learning"},{"time":8000,"text":"that I really wish more people would understand"},{"time":11000,"text":"about the potential of students."},{"time":14000,"text":"In 1931, my grandmother --"},{"time":16000,"text":"bottom left for you guys over here --"},{"time":18000,"text":"graduated from the eighth grade."},{"time":20000,"text":"She went to school to get the information"},{"time":22000,"text":"because that's where the information lived."},{"time":24000,"text":"It was in the books; it was inside the teacher's head;"},{"time":26000,"text":"and she needed to go there to get the information,"},{"time":29000,"text":"because that's how you learned."},{"time":31000,"text":"Fast-forward a generation:"},{"time":33000,"text":"this is the one-room schoolhouse, Oak Grove,"},{"time":35000,"text":"where my father went to a one-room schoolhouse."},{"time":37000,"text":"And he again had to travel to the school"},{"time":39000,"text":"to get the information from the teacher,"},{"time":41000,"text":"stored it in the only portable memory he has, which is inside his own head,"},{"time":44000,"text":"and take it with him,"},{"time":46000,"text":"because that is how information was being transported"},{"time":49000,"text":"from teacher to student and then used in the world."},{"time":52000,"text":"When I was a kid,"},{"time":54000,"text":"we had a set of encyclopedias at my house."},{"time":56000,"text":"It was purchased the year I was born,"},{"time":58000,"text":"and it was extraordinary,"},{"time":60000,"text":"because I did not have to wait to go to the library to get to the information."},{"time":63000,"text":"The information was inside my house"},{"time":65000,"text":"and it was awesome."},{"time":67000,"text":"This was different"},{"time":69000,"text":"than either generation had experienced before,"},{"time":71000,"text":"and it changed the way I interacted with information"},{"time":73000,"text":"even at just a small level."},{"time":75000,"text":"But the information was closer to me."},{"time":77000,"text":"I could get access to it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":79000,"text":"In the time that passes"},{"time":81000,"text":"between when I was a kid in high school"},{"time":83000,"text":"and when I started teaching,"},{"time":85000,"text":"we really see the advent of the Internet."},{"time":87000,"text":"Right about the time that the Internet gets going"},{"time":89000,"text":"as an educational tool,"},{"time":91000,"text":"I take off from Wisconsin"},{"time":93000,"text":"and move to Kansas, small town Kansas,"},{"time":95000,"text":"where I had an opportunity to teach"},{"time":97000,"text":"in a lovely, small-town,"},{"time":99000,"text":"rural Kansas school district,"},{"time":101000,"text":"where I was teaching my favorite subject,"},{"time":103000,"text":"American government."},{"time":105000,"text":"My first year -- super gung-ho -- going to teach American government,"},{"time":108000,"text":"loved the political system."},{"time":110000,"text":"Kids in the 12th grade:"},{"time":112000,"text":"not exactly all that enthusiastic"},{"time":114000,"text":"about the American government system."},{"time":116000,"text":"Year two: learned a few things -- had to change my tactic."},{"time":119000,"text":"And I put in front of them an authentic experience"},{"time":121000,"text":"that allowed them to learn for themselves."},{"time":124000,"text":"I didn't tell them what to do or how to do it."},{"time":126000,"text":"I posed a problem in front of them,"},{"time":128000,"text":"which was to put on an election forum for their own community."}]},{"cues":[{"time":132000,"text":"They produced flyers. They called offices."},{"time":134000,"text":"They checked schedules. They were meeting with secretaries."},{"time":136000,"text":"They produced an election forum booklet"},{"time":138000,"text":"for the entire town to learn more about their candidates."},{"time":140000,"text":"They invited everyone into the school"},{"time":142000,"text":"for an evening of conversation"},{"time":144000,"text":"about government and politics"},{"time":146000,"text":"and whether or not the streets were done well,"},{"time":148000,"text":"and really had this robust experiential learning."},{"time":151000,"text":"The older teachers -- more experienced --"},{"time":153000,"text":"looked at me and went,"},{"time":155000,"text":"\"Oh, there she is. That's so cute. She's trying to get that done.\""},{"time":158000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":160000,"text":"\"She doesn't know what she's in for.\""},{"time":162000,"text":"But I knew that the kids would show up,"},{"time":164000,"text":"and I believed it,"},{"time":166000,"text":"and I told them every week what I expected out of them."},{"time":169000,"text":"And that night, all 90 kids --"},{"time":171000,"text":"dressed appropriately, doing their job, owning it."},{"time":174000,"text":"I had to just sit and watch."},{"time":176000,"text":"It was theirs. It was experiential. It was authentic."},{"time":178000,"text":"It meant something to them."},{"time":180000,"text":"And they will step up."}]},{"cues":[{"time":182000,"text":"From Kansas, I moved on to lovely Arizona,"},{"time":185000,"text":"where I taught in Flagstaff for a number of years,"},{"time":188000,"text":"this time with middle school students."},{"time":190000,"text":"Luckily, I didn't have to teach them American government."},{"time":192000,"text":"Could teach them the more exciting topic of geography."},{"time":195000,"text":"Again, \"thrilled\" to learn."},{"time":199000,"text":"But what was interesting"},{"time":201000,"text":"about this position I found myself in in Arizona,"},{"time":204000,"text":"was I had this really"},{"time":206000,"text":"extraordinarily eclectic group of kids to work with"},{"time":208000,"text":"in a truly public school,"},{"time":210000,"text":"and we got to have these moments where we would get these opportunities."},{"time":213000,"text":"And one opportunity"},{"time":215000,"text":"was we got to go and meet Paul Rusesabagina,"},{"time":218000,"text":"which is the gentleman"},{"time":220000,"text":"that the movie \"Hotel Rwanda\" is based after."},{"time":222000,"text":"And he was going to speak at the high school next door to us."},{"time":224000,"text":"We could walk there. We didn't even have to pay for the buses."},{"time":226000,"text":"There was no expense cost. Perfect field trip."}]},{"cues":[{"time":229000,"text":"The problem then becomes"},{"time":231000,"text":"how do you take seventh- and eighth-graders to a talk about genocide"},{"time":233000,"text":"and deal with the subject in a way"},{"time":235000,"text":"that is responsible and respectful,"},{"time":237000,"text":"and they know what to do with it."},{"time":239000,"text":"And so we chose to look at Paul Rusesabagina"},{"time":241000,"text":"as an example of a gentleman"},{"time":243000,"text":"who singularly used his life to do something positive."},{"time":247000,"text":"I then challenged the kids to identify"},{"time":249000,"text":"someone in their own life, or in their own story, or in their own world,"},{"time":252000,"text":"that they could identify that had done a similar thing."},{"time":254000,"text":"I asked them to produce a little movie about it."},{"time":256000,"text":"It's the first time we'd done this."},{"time":258000,"text":"Nobody really knew how to make these little movies on the computer,"},{"time":260000,"text":"but they were into it. And I asked them to put their own voice over it."},{"time":264000,"text":"It was the most awesome moment of revelation"},{"time":269000,"text":"that when you ask kids to use their own voice"},{"time":272000,"text":"and ask them to speak for themselves,"},{"time":274000,"text":"what they're willing to share."},{"time":276000,"text":"The last question of the assignment is:"},{"time":278000,"text":"how do you plan to use your life"},{"time":280000,"text":"to positively impact other people?"},{"time":282000,"text":"The things that kids will say"},{"time":284000,"text":"when you ask them and take the time to listen"},{"time":287000,"text":"is extraordinary."}]},{"cues":[{"time":290000,"text":"Fast-forward to Pennsylvania, where I find myself today."},{"time":293000,"text":"I teach at the Science Leadership Academy,"},{"time":295000,"text":"which is a partnership school between the Franklin Institute"},{"time":298000,"text":"and the school district of Philadelphia."},{"time":300000,"text":"We are a nine through 12 public school,"},{"time":303000,"text":"but we do school quite differently."},{"time":306000,"text":"I moved there primarily"},{"time":308000,"text":"to be part of a learning environment"},{"time":310000,"text":"that validated the way that I knew that kids learned,"},{"time":312000,"text":"and that really wanted to investigate"},{"time":314000,"text":"what was possible"},{"time":316000,"text":"when you are willing to let go"},{"time":318000,"text":"of some of the paradigms of the past,"},{"time":320000,"text":"of information scarcity when my grandmother was in school"},{"time":323000,"text":"and when my father was in school and even when I was in school,"},{"time":326000,"text":"and to a moment when we have information surplus."},{"time":328000,"text":"So what do you do when the information is all around you?"},{"time":331000,"text":"Why do you have kids come to school"},{"time":333000,"text":"if they no longer have to come there to get the information?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":336000,"text":"In Philadelphia we have a one-to-one laptop program,"},{"time":339000,"text":"so the kids are bringing in laptops with them everyday,"},{"time":342000,"text":"taking them home, getting access to information."},{"time":345000,"text":"And here's the thing that you need to get comfortable with"},{"time":348000,"text":"when you've given the tool"},{"time":350000,"text":"to acquire information to students,"},{"time":352000,"text":"is that you have to be comfortable with this idea"},{"time":354000,"text":"of allowing kids to fail"},{"time":356000,"text":"as part of the learning process."},{"time":359000,"text":"We deal right now in the educational landscape"},{"time":361000,"text":"with an infatuation"},{"time":363000,"text":"with the culture of one right answer"},{"time":365000,"text":"that can be properly bubbled on the average multiple choice test,"},{"time":368000,"text":"and I am here to share with you:"},{"time":370000,"text":"it is not learning."},{"time":372000,"text":"That is the absolute wrong thing to ask,"},{"time":375000,"text":"to tell kids to never be wrong."},{"time":377000,"text":"To ask them to always have the right answer"},{"time":380000,"text":"doesn't allow them to learn."},{"time":382000,"text":"So we did this project,"},{"time":384000,"text":"and this is one of the artifacts of the project."},{"time":386000,"text":"I almost never show them off"},{"time":388000,"text":"because of the issue of the idea of failure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":390000,"text":"My students produced these info-graphics"},{"time":392000,"text":"as a result of a unit that we decided to do at the end of the year"},{"time":395000,"text":"responding to the oil spill."},{"time":397000,"text":"I asked them to take the examples that we were seeing"},{"time":400000,"text":"of the info-graphics that existed"},{"time":402000,"text":"in a lot of mass media,"},{"time":404000,"text":"and take a look at what were the interesting components of it,"},{"time":407000,"text":"and produce one for themselves"},{"time":409000,"text":"of a different man-made disaster from American history."},{"time":411000,"text":"And they had certain criteria to do it."},{"time":413000,"text":"They were a little uncomfortable with it,"},{"time":415000,"text":"because we'd never done this before, and they didn't know exactly how to do it."},{"time":417000,"text":"They can talk -- they're very smooth,"},{"time":419000,"text":"and they can write very, very well,"},{"time":421000,"text":"but asking them to communicate ideas in a different way"},{"time":424000,"text":"was a little uncomfortable for them."},{"time":427000,"text":"But I gave them the room to just do the thing."},{"time":430000,"text":"Go create. Go figure it out."},{"time":432000,"text":"Let's see what we can do."},{"time":434000,"text":"And the student that persistently"},{"time":436000,"text":"turns out the best visual product did not disappoint."},{"time":439000,"text":"This was done in like two or three days."},{"time":441000,"text":"And this is the work of the student that consistently did it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":444000,"text":"And when I sat the students down, I said, \"Who's got the best one?\""},{"time":447000,"text":"And they immediately went, \"There it is.\""},{"time":449000,"text":"Didn't read anything. \"There it is.\""},{"time":451000,"text":"And I said, \"Well what makes it great?\""},{"time":453000,"text":"And they're like, \"Oh, the design's good, and he's using good color."},{"time":455000,"text":"And there's some ... \" And they went through all that we processed out loud."},{"time":458000,"text":"And I said, \"Go read it.\""},{"time":460000,"text":"And they're like, \"Oh, that one wasn't so awesome.\""},{"time":463000,"text":"And then we went to another one --"},{"time":465000,"text":"it didn't have great visuals, but it had great information --"},{"time":467000,"text":"and spent an hour talking about the learning process,"},{"time":470000,"text":"because it wasn't about whether or not it was perfect,"},{"time":472000,"text":"or whether or not it was what I could create."},{"time":474000,"text":"It asked them to create for themselves,"},{"time":477000,"text":"and it allowed them to fail,"},{"time":479000,"text":"process, learn from."},{"time":481000,"text":"And when we do another round of this in my class this year,"},{"time":483000,"text":"they will do better this time,"},{"time":485000,"text":"because learning"},{"time":487000,"text":"has to include an amount of failure,"},{"time":490000,"text":"because failure is instructional"},{"time":492000,"text":"in the process."}]},{"cues":[{"time":494000,"text":"There are a million pictures"},{"time":497000,"text":"that I could click through here,"},{"time":499000,"text":"and had to choose carefully -- this is one of my favorites --"},{"time":502000,"text":"of students learning,"},{"time":504000,"text":"of what learning can look like"},{"time":506000,"text":"in a landscape where we let go of the idea"},{"time":509000,"text":"that kids have to come to school to get the information,"},{"time":511000,"text":"but instead, ask them what they can do with it."},{"time":513000,"text":"Ask them really interesting questions."},{"time":515000,"text":"They will not disappoint."},{"time":517000,"text":"Ask them to go to places,"},{"time":519000,"text":"to see things for themselves,"},{"time":521000,"text":"to actually experience the learning,"},{"time":523000,"text":"to play, to inquire."},{"time":526000,"text":"This is one of my favorite photos,"},{"time":528000,"text":"because this was taken on Tuesday,"},{"time":530000,"text":"when I asked the students to go to the polls."},{"time":532000,"text":"This is Robbie, and this was his first day of voting,"},{"time":535000,"text":"and he wanted to share that with everybody and do that."},{"time":537000,"text":"But this is learning too,"},{"time":539000,"text":"because we asked them to go out into real spaces."}]},{"cues":[{"time":545000,"text":"The main point"},{"time":547000,"text":"is that, if we continue to look at education"},{"time":550000,"text":"as if it's about coming to school"},{"time":553000,"text":"to get the information"},{"time":555000,"text":"and not about experiential learning,"},{"time":557000,"text":"empowering student voice and embracing failure,"},{"time":560000,"text":"we're missing the mark."},{"time":562000,"text":"And everything that everybody is talking about today"},{"time":564000,"text":"isn't possible if we keep having an educational system"},{"time":567000,"text":"that does not value these qualities,"},{"time":570000,"text":"because we won't get there with a standardized test,"},{"time":572000,"text":"and we won't get there with a culture of one right answer."},{"time":574000,"text":"We know how to do this better,"},{"time":576000,"text":"and it's time to do better."}]},{"cues":[{"time":578000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}